1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the incorporation of wireless charging into existing wireless communication systems and its network applications. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses technical standards and power management, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses scheduling strategies and deployment strategies, which are related to control systems. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper discusses mobile charger dispatch strategies, which can be related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but it is possible as the paper discusses the practical future network applications of wireless charging, which can be related to the societal impact of technology.
